      "Moving away and migrating to Tehran, expanding relationships and progressing in life-that was not the mistake.\nThe mistake was the way I thought about it, the imagination and the intention behind it.",
      "I lost certain qualities.\nI weakened and destroyed various relationships.\nA self-chosen distance.\nAnd I regretted it.",
      "Everything, in practice and on paper, went well.\nScientific progress, professional advancement, specialization, income-everything.",
      "But long-standing friendships filled with memories and depth faded away and disappeared.\nBetter performance, greater achievements-yet often weaker spiritual and emotional quality.\nFewer attachments. Weaker ones.",
      "The turning point came when one of my close friends died in 2020.\nI had been distant from him for several years.\nThe regret for all the days and memories we could have created together during those years-but did not-collapsed upon me, and even now I have not fully digested it. The weight of it has never been lifted from my shoulders.",
      "Now I think that once again I may have taken the same path-only on a far larger scale.",
      "This time I fled from my own country and continent.\nFor progress, for growth, for expanding possibilities, experiences, and relationships-and for everything else.\nYet perhaps also out of deep exhaustion, emotional weariness, and disillusionment with the environment and the people around me.",
      "What if this pattern repeats itself again?",
      "What if in a few years I once again find myself wanting to escape the moment-tired of everything and everyone?",
      "Now I see all the signs of homesickness within myself.\nUnconsciously, at night I dream of relatives, friends, and classmates.\nThe same people and gatherings I once seemed to be counting the days to leave behind.",
