      "**Wednesday – 12:58**",
      "I am caught in a deeply strange contradiction.",
      "On one hand, I profoundly need solitude.\nFrom the bottom of my heart, I want to disappear from the stage of life.\nTo sink into silence and stillness, and not worry about any event, judgment, or thought.\nTo simply pause, and drift into reflection.\nNo one to know me.\nNo one to wait for me.\nNothing expected of me, no responsibility to carry.\nPure stillness and slowness.\nAmple time to process events and my inner states.\nWhich, of course, is not possible.",
      "On the other hand, the most toxic and harmful thing for me right now is solitude.",
      "One day, I become intensely alone; the weight of the world’s sorrow takes over my entire being, and it leads nowhere—no resolution, no relief.\nEven the knot in my throat refuses to break, so that at least some of the pressure could be released.",
      "Thoughts, fears, anxiety, and grief consume me like a black hole, and no struggle or effort seems to offer a way out.",
      "Another day, I become surrounded—filled with conversations and people.\nSometimes even intentionally, I say yes to every invitation and plan, just to spend more and more time with others, to avoid being alone, to keep my mind from being entirely under my own control.\nIn the end, late at night, against my own will, I return home alone, face my solitude, and with overwhelming exhaustion, think only of sleep and rest—so I can begin again tomorrow.",
      "Crowdedness until the very last moments of the day.",
      "Time passes more easily.\nThe mind feels lighter.\nBut less gets done.\nFewer things move forward.\nThere is less room left for personal work.",
      "A strange contradiction.\nA need and desire for absolute solitude, yet at the same time an awareness of its harm.",
      "And still, I have not found my truly safe people, or a space where I can express myself fully, without fear or concern.\nPerhaps I never will.\nPerhaps I never should fully reveal my true self.",
      "What would happen if others knew how much darkness, sadness, and depression pass through the depths of my thoughts and emotions?\nWould they be afraid, withdraw, see me as weak—and leave me even more alone?",
      "And yet, I cannot ignore or suppress my emotional and psychological needs.\nSo far, I have found no solution, no help.",
      "The friends I have back in my own country, even through distance and digital connection, were to a large extent that safe space for me—easing loneliness and homesickness.\nBut for some time now, they have had no access to the internet, and I am completely cut off from them.",
      "Tonight, without realizing it beforehand, it was Chaharshanbe Suri.\nI am not particularly a person of rituals or special occasions, except for a few rare and meaningful ones.\nBut the fact that I had completely forgotten this day and its date was painful.\nHow far and how lost had I become, to forget such a day?\nAnd how disordered and sorrowful everything must be, that this historic and memorable occasion did not even carry the feeling of its arrival.",
      "Now, how difficult it is to explain this day—its meaning and emotional weight—to my new, non-Iranian friends, so that perhaps they might understand even a fraction of it.",
